The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Honeymoon gift to Mahajan
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Honeymoon gift to Mahajan
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                                              Rahul Mahajan and Dimpy Ganguly      
	New Delhi, March 9: After marriage on national TV, its honeymoon in picturesque Maldives for Rahul Mahajan.        
	A court here today agreed to release Rahuls passport, confiscated since he was granted bail in a 2006 drug abuse case, provided he furnished a fixed deposit of Rs 5 lakh and a personal bond of the same amount.        
	After his Maldives trip, which is to end on March 30, the son of late BJP leader Pramod Mahajan is expected to visit Calcutta with his Bengali bride Dimpy Ganguly whom he had married on reality show Rahul Dulhaniya Le Jayenge on March 6.        
	The TV programme, the third in a string of reality shows Rahul has been a part of in the past two years, fetched the channel 1.42 crore viewers on its final day. The three-hour, 15-minute episode showed him not only choosing his bride but also marrying her.        
	Rahul and Dimpy had both been in the courtroom yesterday but today he arrived alone. The additional sessions judge asked him to sign an undertaking stating he would not take part in any kind of shooting during his stay abroad.        
	The court also told him to get his marriage registered under the Hindu Marriage Act.        
	The drug case against Rahul was lodged after he and his late fathers secretary, Vivek Moitra, were admitted to Apollo Hospital here on June 2, 2006. They had allegedly taken drugs laced with alcohol at Pramod Mahajans then official residence. Moitra died in hospital.                                                                                                                                                          
